AVD CONNECTION FLOW azure AD
1. Session host maintains outbound connection to RD Broker
2. User requests feed
User authenticates with Entra ID
Gets token
Token sent to RD Web
RD Web queries Broker
Broker checks Geographical DB
Returns RDP files/icons
3.User starts connection
Connection goes to Azure Front Door
Redirected to nearest Gateway
4.Broker orchestrates session host connection
5.Connection Types
REVERSE CONNECT (DEFAULT)
Uses TCP
Gateway relays traffic
RDP SHORTPATH
Uses direct UDP connection
Bypasses gateway

